thread.title: Grain lower, livestock mostly lower

title: Grain lower, livestock mostly lower
text:
Tue, Jul 28, 2015, 2:41 AM AEST - Australia Markets open in 7 hrs 19 mins Grain lower, livestock mostly lower Grain lower on the CBOT, beef mostly lower, pork lower on the CME Associated Press – 1 hour 50 minutes ago Recommend Print 
CHICAGO (AP) -- Grain futures were lower Friday in early trading on the Chicago Board of Trade. 
Wheat for September delivery was 2.50 cents lower at $5.0920 a bushel; December corn was 11.50 cents lower at $3.91 a bushel; December oats were 5.50 cents lower at $2.3660 bushel; while November soybeans were 17 cents lower at 9.48 cents a bushel. 
Beef was mostly lower and pork lower on the Chicago Mercantile Exchange. 
October live cattle was .03 cent higher at $1.4415 a pound; August feeder cattle was .38 cent lower at $2.0930 a pound; October lean hogs lost .95 cent to $.6308 a pound. @y7finance on Twitter, become a fan on Facebook Aussies to work longer, need to save more AAP
